# ✅ 🔥 DevOps Python Modules Mapping (Final Table)

***

## 🧠 Core System & Automation

| Task               | Module       | What it does + Examples                                                |
| ------------------ | ------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| System interaction | `os`         | OS operations → `os.cpu_count()`, `os.getloadavg()`, `os.system("ls")` |
| Script control     | `sys`        | Exit codes, args → `sys.exit(0/1/2)`, `sys.argv`                       |
| Run commands       | `subprocess` | Run Linux commands → `df -h`, `free -m`, `systemctl status`            |
| File + Disk        | `shutil`     | Disk usage, copy files → `disk_usage("/")`, `copy()`, `move()`         |
| System monitoring  | `psutil`     | CPU %, memory %, disk %, processes, network stats                      |
| Path handling      | `pathlib`    | File paths → `/tmp/file.txt`, check exists                             |
| CLI arguments      | `argparse`   | Pass input → `--host`, `--threshold`, `--file`                         |

***

## 🌐 Networking & API Interaction

| Task               | Module     | What it does + Examples                         |
| ------------------ | ---------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| Network connection | `socket`   | TCP/port check → port 80/443, connectivity test |
| SSL handling       | `ssl`      | Certificates, HTTPS validation                  |
| HTTP (basic)       | `urllib`   | Built-in API calls                              |
| API calls          | `requests` | REST APIs → `GET/POST`, JSON handling           |
| SSH automation     | `paramiko` | SSH login, run remote commands                  |
| Remote automation  | `fabric`   | Execute commands on servers (wrapper over SSH)  |

***

## ⏱️ Time & Scheduling

| Task          | Module     | What it does + Examples              |
| ------------- | ---------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Sleep / delay | `time`     | `time.sleep(10)` → cron-like scripts |
| Date/time     | `datetime` | timestamps, logs, scheduling         |

***

## 📄 Text Parsing & Config

| Task             | Module         | What it does + Examples               |
| ---------------- | -------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| JSON parsing     | `json`         | API responses → `json.loads()`        |
| Pattern matching | `re`           | Regex → logs parsing, extract values  |
| Config files     | `configparser` | Read `.ini` → DB configs, app configs |
| CSV handling     | `csv`          | Read/write CSV files                  |
| YAML parsing     | `PyYAML`       | Kubernetes, Ansible configs           |

***

## ☁️ Cloud & Containers

| Task             | Module                 | What it does + Examples            |
| ---------------- | ---------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| AWS automation   | `boto3`                | EC2 start/stop, S3 upload/download |
| GCP storage      | `google-cloud-storage` | Upload/download objects            |
| Azure automation | `azure-mgmt`           | Manage resources (VM, storage)     |
| Container mgmt   | `docker`               | Start/stop containers              |
| Kubernetes       | `kubernetes`           | Manage pods, deployments           |

***

## 🔐 Logging, Env & Security

| Task          | Module          | What it does + Examples                  |
| ------------- | --------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| Logging       | `logging`       | logs → INFO, ERROR, DEBUG                |
| Hashing       | `hashlib`       | SHA256, MD5 (password hashing, checksum) |
| Secure tokens | `secrets`       | generate passwords, API tokens           |
| Encryption    | `cryptography`  | certificates, encrypt/decrypt data       |
| Env variables | `python-dotenv` | load `.env` → secrets, configs           |

